<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>2-381.21</num>
  <heading>Electronic transactions.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Notwithstanding any other provisions of this chapter, the CPO may acquire supplies and services through:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>Electronic solicitation and bid response; or</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>Electronic auctions.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>In selecting one of the methods authorized by this section, upon proper validation and authorization, a contracting officer may accept electronic signatures for all electronic commerce transactions.</text>
  </para>
